President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Utah due to severe winter storms and flooding that occurred between December 20-24, 2010. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in Kane and Washington Counties. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has named William J. Doran III as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations for federal assistance may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.